You are tasked with creating a simple iOS app that utilizes Combine framework to handle button tap events. The app should consist of a single view with a button, and upon tapping the button, a label should display the number of times the button has been tapped. You are required to implement the necessary code to achieve this functionality using Swift and Combine framework.

Your task is to complete the implementation of the ViewController class, which includes setting up the button, label, and the Combine publisher for the button tap events. You should also subscribe to the tap events and update the label with the number of taps.

```swift
import UIKit
import Combine

class ViewController: UIViewController {
    private var button: UIButton!
    private var label: UILabel!
    private var tapCount = 0
    private var cancellables = Set<AnyCancellable>()

    override func viewDidLoad() {
        super.viewDidLoad()

        // Create and configure the button
        button = UIButton(type: .system)
        button.setTitle("Tap Me", for: .normal)
        button.translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints = false
        view.addSubview(button)

        // Create and configure the label
        label = UILabel()
        label.text = "Taps: 0"
        label.translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints = false
        view.addSubview(label)

        // Set button constraints
        NSLayoutConstraint.activate([
            button.centerXAnchor.constraint(equalTo: view.centerXAnchor),
            button.centerYAnchor.constraint(equalTo: view.centerYAnchor),
        ])

        // Set label constraints
        NSLayoutConstraint.activate([
            label.topAnchor.constraint(equalTo: button.bottomAnchor, constant: 20),
            label.centerXAnchor.constraint(equalTo: view.centerXAnchor),
        ])

        // Create a publisher for button tap events
        let tapPublisher = button.tapPublisher

        // Subscribe to tap events and update the label
        tapPublisher
            .sink { [weak self] _ in
                self?.tapCount += 1
                self?.label.text = "Taps: \(self?.tapCount ?? 0)"
            }
            .store(in: &cancellables)
    }
}
```

