    return <div>Hello, World!</div>;
}

// Wrap MyComponent with withRenderTimeLogging HOC
const MyComponentWithLogging = withRenderTimeLogging(MyComponent);

// Render the wrapped component
ReactDOM.render(<MyComponentWithLogging />, document.getElementById('root'));
```

When `MyComponent` is rendered, the time taken for rendering will be logged to the console, fulfilling the requirements of the problem.

